		<part id="microservices">
			<title>Microservices</title>
			<slide id="microservices-definition">
				<title>Microservice Definition</title>
				<blockquote>
					<p>A microservice is an independently deployable component of bounded scope that supports interoperability through message-based communication. Microservice architecture is a style of engineering highly automated, evolvable software systems made up of capability-aligned microservices. <span style="font-size : 75% ;">(Irakli Nadareishvili, Ronnie Mitra, Matt McLarty, and Mike Amundsen, <q>Microservice Architecture</q>, O'Reilly, 2016)</span></p>
